Geoff Haigh wanted to marry his partner of 26 years Heather after being diagnosed with terminal pancreatic cancer . 
  Mr Haigh, 61, from Oldham, Greater Manchester, wanted to wed in November last year . 
  But the couple were left with three marriage certificates as the first two were invalid . 
  Guests were forced to listen to the wedding song 10 times in a row and their marriage certificate was recorded with the wrong date . 
  Geoff Haigh died weeks after the ceremony in January this year . 
  Mr and Mrs Haigh had planned to marry after he was diagnosed with cancer . 
  He wanted to get married after being told he had terminal cancer and was too ill to fly . 
  He and his wife Heather were married in Manchester